				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-659029#post-4753005</guid>
				<title>SUCKERS</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-659029/scp-1710#post-4753005</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 21 Aug 2020 01:54:43 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Twisted_Code</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1665218</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>you had me long before I saw the note about the acrostic and read sideways, but that just sealed the deal. While this probably isn't going to be one of my top 5 like SCP-3008 (&quot;A Perfectly Normal, Regular Old IKEA&quot;), I thought the juxtaposition of the characters was cute. Was Maxwell (or whatever their &quot;true name&quot; is) formerly some form of wildlife (or an entire collective thereof)? I noticed a lot of mentioning of sharpening not unlike a deer's antlers (though I'm not sure what to make of the comparisons to metal), and a mention of &quot;our acorns&quot; like squirrels and chipmunks often collect as food. Maybe I'm misreading but that seemed like a hint.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
